observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the LCE to direct the:
(a) Municipal Inventory Committee to:
i. prioritize the preparation and/or reconstruction of property records and registries;
ii. establish accountability on properties through issuance and monitoring of AREs for each recorded PPEs;
iii. assign property tags and property numbers to each PPE item adopting the prescribed numbering system of COA Circular No. 2020-006; and
(b) Municipal Appraisal and Disposal Committee to perform the mandated procedures for the disposal of the identified unserviceable properties.

We recommended that the LCE instruct the GAD FP to:
(a) carefully plan the corresponding budget allocations of GAD PPAs by preparing project breakdown of expenses before the approval of the plan and budget;
(b) create a multi-year GAD Agenda as basis for the annual GAD Plans and Budget by using the templates provided in PCW Memorandum Circular No. 2018-04 dated September 19, 2018;
(c) conduct a review after three years and an end-term evaluation to reflect on the status of accomplishment, variances, and overall assessment of the implementation of the GAD agenda based on the goals and desired results/ outcomes, and report thereon using the prescribed format; and
(d) use the HGDG tool to properly identify the gender issues on LGU PPAs or its portion that can be attributed to GAD Activities

We recommended that the LCE instruct the MENRO to:
(a) regularly assess, monitor and update, as warranted the SWMP projections on waste and revenue generation;
(b) encourage stakeholders to actively participate in minimizing waste generation through regular IEC activities;
(c) ensure that the MRFs and other SWM facilities, if any, function exclusively as intended; and
(d) consider providing technical and/or financial support to barangays with the view of establishing the required number of MRFs in the standard desired.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to instruct the:

  Designated Property Officer to (i) maintain Property Cards for each type of properties in coordination with the Office of the Municipal Accountant; 

(ii) prepare the necessary documents for the disposal of unserviceable properties; 

and (iii) maintain Local Road Inventory and Road Map and Local Road Network Property Card; 



Municipal Accountant, in close coordination with the designated Property Officer and RHU representative, to (i) exert effort in securing all the turnover documents or deeds of donation for properties donated by DOH and recognize the same in the books of accounts simultaneous with the fixing of accountability therefor; and (ii) limit the recorded parcels of land only to those over which the municipality has valid claim;


Municipal Engineering Office to provide the Municipal Accountant and the designated Property Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects and, on the basis of which, the Municipal Accountant to record the same in the books of accounts; and

Municipal Treasurer (or General Services Officer) to secure proofs of ownership for untitled lands claimed by the Municipality to avoid future third party claims.

We recommended and the LCE agreed to instruct the:
RHU and MDRRMO to submit to the MT the RIS for any request of goods under their custody;
MT to consolidate the RIS and submit the report to the Accounting Office;
Designated Property Officer and MA to maintain the required inventory records to facilitate determination of stock position as at any given date;
Inventory Committee headed by the Property Officer - Designate to conduct the physical inventory and reconcile the results thereof with the account balances reported by the Accounting Unit, and submit the same to the Office of the COA Audit Team on or before the required period; and
MA to draw a Journal Entry Voucher (JEV) to recognize the movement of Welfare Goods, or any inventoriable supplies for that matter, for the accurate reporting on the balances of inventories as at end of any reporting period.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to instruct the:
Municipal Accountant to (i) submit the accomplished SAC Forms, barangay certification, printed copy of properly labeled pictures of the beneficiaries during actual receipt of the assistance and valid IDs of the beneficiaries in close coordination with the MSWDO; and (ii) recognize any grant pursuant to authoritative issuance/s related thereto;
Municipal Treasurer to draw a cash advance based on the amount of the approved payroll;
MSWD Officer to (i) exert effort in securing a copy of all the supporting documents submitted to DPEO and submit the same to the Municipal Accountant; and (ii) explain the inconsistencies noted between the paid payrolls and the uploaded SAC Forms of three beneficiaries; and
Municipal-link to coordinate with other government agencies in the implementation of parallel amelioration programs to avoid duplication of payments.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive, in his capacity as Chairman of the GFPS, agreed to undertake the following courses of actions:

issue amendatory order to complete the composition of the GFPS, including its ExeCom, and TWG pursuant to Annex A of the JMC to facilitate and maximize gender mainstreaming efforts;


prepare and submit complete GAD AR based on the GPB to facilitate thorough evaluation of the PPAs implemented out of the GAD Fund; 


instruct the GFPS to gather GAD information such as gender statistics and sex-disaggregated data to serve as inputs for planning, budgeting, programming and policy formulation for the setting up and maintenance of GAD database; and


conduct annual or regular monitoring of the accomplishments in order to evaluate the utilization and outcome of the GAD budget in terms of its impact and influence on the implementation of gender-responsive PPAs pursuant to Section 5.0 and Annex H of the JMC.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to instruct the:
Designated Property Officer to (i) maintain Property Cards for each type of properties in coordination with the Office of the Municipal Accountant; (ii) prepare the necessary documents for the disposal of unserviceable properties; and (iii) maintain Local Road Inventory and Road Map and Local Road Network Property Card;
Municipal Accountant, in close coordination with the designated Property Officer and RHU representative, to (a) exert effort in securing all the turnover documents or deeds of donation for properties donated by DOH and recognize the same in the books of accounts simultaneous with the fixing of accountability therefor; and (b) limiting the recorded parcels of land only to those over which the municipality has valid claim;
Municipal Engineering Office to provide the Municipal Accountant and the designated Property Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects and, on the basis of which, the Municipal Accountant to record the same in the books of accounts; and
Municipal Treasurer (or General Services Officer) to secure proofs of ownership for untitled lands claimed by the Municipality to avoid future third party claims.

We recommended and the Local Chief Executive, in his capacity as Chairman of the GFPS, agreed to undertake the following courses of actions:
issue amendatory order to complete the composition of the GFPS, including its ExeCom, and TWG pursuant to Annex A of the JMC to facilitate and maximize gender mainstreaming efforts;
prepare and submit complete GAD AR based on the GPB to facilitate thorough evaluation of the PPAs implemented out of the GAD Fund;
instruct the GFPS to gather GAD information such as gender statistics and sex-disaggregated data to serve as inputs for planning, budgeting, programming and policy formulation for the setting up and maintenance of GAD database; and
conduct annual or regular monitoring of the accomplishments in order to evaluate the utilization and outcome of the GAD budget in terms of its impact and influence on the implementation of gender-responsive PPAs pursuant to Section 5.0 and Annex H of the JMC.

We recommended that the Local Chief Executive:

require Municipal Treasurer to furnish the Municipal Accountant a duly signed certified list showing the name of taxpayers and the amount due and collectible every beginning of the year for recording purposes; 

instruct the Municipal Accountant to draw a JEV to record the RPT/SET receivables based on the certified list from the Office of the Municipal Treasurer and ensure that the recorded receivables are based on actual reference documents;

encourage the involvement of barangay officials in the tax campaign to reach out to a larger area; and 

intensify tax collections thru formulating strategies to improve collection of real property taxes.

We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed to:

properly establish the GAD Focal Point System with Technical Working Group and Executive Committee;

send all members of the GFPS including elected local officials and department heads to capacity building programs and GAD seminars;

encourage all members of the GFPS to function and discharge their duties accordingly; and

instruct the members of the GFPS to (i) prepare proposal for PPAs earlier to give proper time for their review and approval; and (ii) analyze each activities for appropriate allocation of fund.
